Function: 
		It is a set of statements or block of code to ececute a task.
		It helps to break a large program into smaller part 
		Which helps developer to debug the program easily	
		In Javascript we define a function using "function" keyword.
		We can define more than one  function in a file, and we can call a function more than one time.
		We cannot define a function inside anoother function.

Function Naming convensions/ Rules 
1. function name always starts with alphabet
2. function name can be alphanumeric
3. Function name cannot contain only numbers 
4. Function name cannot starts with a number
5. Function name cannot contain space ex[get data()] X
6. Function name cannot contain any special character except underscore 
	get_data()
7. Try to keep Function name like this: getData();
	camelCase
________________________________________________________________________________________

Types of functions in Javascript:
1. Predefine Function 	: Funcitons which are already defined. 
								OR
						  Function whose definition is already define and we only need to call.
Ex:		prompt(), parseInt(), 

2. User Define Function : Functions which are defined by the user.
	Types of user define functions

	1. Parameterized Function
	2. Non-Parameterized Function
	3. Function with return keyword
	4. Function with default parameters 
_______________________________________________________________________________________

1. Paremeterized Function: Functions with parameters 
Syntax:
// function definition
		function functionName(parameters sperated by comma)
		{
				Statements;
		}
//function calling 

		functionName(values seprated by comma);


2. Non-parameterize : Function without parameters 

	// function definition
		function functionName()
		{
			statements;
		}

		// Function calling

		functionName();



	

